# calc_1_plus_2.numos — type "1+2", evaluate, screenshot, and ASSERT the result.
#
# Drives CalculationApp through the SAME dispatch path as live SDL input: open
# the (centered, default-focused) Calculation card, type 1 + 2, press ENTER, let
# the result render, screenshot, then make SEMANTIC assertions.
#
# Phase 4A proved scripted input is deterministic. Phase 4B-C adds the semantic
# proof: instead of only trusting a golden image, we read the value NumOS
# actually computed and assert it equals 3 — no OCR, no pixel matching. The probe
# reads CalculationApp's evaluated ExactVal through an emulator-only read-only
# accessor (NATIVE_SIM); see NativeHal::formatExactVal.
#
# Note: assert_result checks the COMPUTED value, not the rendered pixels. Visual
# correctness (does the 2D layout draw "3") is the separate, human-gated golden
# flow (Phase 4B-A/B) — assertions and goldens are complementary, not redundant.
#
# Timing notes (deterministic, step-ms 16):
#   * 200 frames  -> splash (~frame 125) is safely done; we are in the launcher.
#   * 60 frames   -> Calculation screen load + fade settles after ENTER.
#   * 120 frames  -> evaluation result is composed and rendered.
# Each `key` consumes exactly one frame, so total << the --frames budget below.
#
# Run:
#   program --headless --deterministic --script tests/emulator/scripts/calc_1_plus_2.numos \
#           --frames 1400 --screenshot out/calc_1_plus_2.ppm --quiet
# Exit codes: 0 ok · 2 script/parse error · 3 screenshot write error · 4 assertion failure.

log "calc_1_plus_2: waiting for launcher"
wait 200

# Open Calculation (appId 0 — always dead-center-visible on power-on).
key ENTER
wait 60

# Type the expression 1 + 2.
key 1
key +
key 2

# Evaluate and let the result render.
key ENTER
wait 120

# Screenshot FIRST: the deferred capture happens on this frame, before the
# asserts run on later frames, so the artifact is produced even if an assertion
# then fails.
screenshot out/calc_1_plus_2.ppm
log "calc_1_plus_2: screenshot captured"

# Semantic assertions (Phase 4B-C): the active app is Calculation, the result
# evaluated without error, and the computed value is exactly 3.
assert_app Calculation
assert_no_error
assert_result 3
log "calc_1_plus_2: assertions passed (result == 3)"
